The Nigerian Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced Twenty new confirmed cases of COVID19 in the country. NCDC says as at 09:50 pm 13th April there are 343 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria, 91 have been discharged with 10 deaths The NCDC observed that out of the twenty new cases, 13 were recorded in Lagos, 2 in Edo, 2 in Kano, 2 in Ogun and 1 in Ondo President Muhammadu Buhari had during a national broadcast yesterday extended the lockdown in Lagos, Ogun and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) by another 14 days.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .